The standard gem brings the ethos of StandardJS Â» https://standardjs.com to
Ruby. Itâ€™s a linter & formatter built on
RuboCop Â» https://github.com/rubocop/rubocop and provides an unconfigurable
configuration to all of RuboCopâ€™s built-in rules as well as those included in
rubocop-performance Â» https://github.com/rubocop/rubocop-performance. It also
supports plugins built with
lint_roller Â» https://github.com/standardrb/lint_roller, like
standard-rails Â» https://github.com/standardrb/standard-rails and
standard-sorbet Â» https://github.com/standardrb/standard-sorbet.

Standard Ruby was created and is maintained by the team at Test
Double Â» https://testdouble.com, because we appreciate the importance of
balancing predictable, consistent code with preserving developer autonomy. ğŸ’š

